entries.title: Israel, Palestinians Caught in Escalating Cycle of Violence in Jerusalem and West Bank
entries.description: The situation has deteriorated after two gun attacks in Jerusalem and a wave of Israeli raids in the West Bank.

entries.title: U.K. Prime Minister Fires Top Official Over Tax Probe
entries.description: Rishi Sunak removed Nadhim Zahawi as chairman of the U.K.’s ruling Conservative Party after an ethics report concluded Mr. Zahawi failed to disclose an investigation into his tax affairs last year.

entries.title: Israel Strikes Iran Amid International Push to Contain Tehran
entries.description: Israel carried out a drone strike targeting a defense compound in Iran, as the U.S. and Israel look for ways to contain Tehran’s nuclear and military ambitions.

entries.title: China's Top Nuclear-Weapons Lab Used U.S. Chips Decades After Ban
entries.description: The state-owned institute has continued buying computer chips made by Intel and Nvidia despite its inclusion on a U.S. export blacklist in 1997.

entries.title: On Europe's Border With Russia, Guards Combat Forbidden Trade
entries.description: Customs agents in Finland work to enforce Western sanctions on exports, blocking shipments of items from luxury cars to sonar gear.

entries.title: Ukraine Asks for Longer-Range Missiles as It Awaits Tank Deliveries
entries.description: Kyiv called on its Western backers to supply weapons capable of striking deeper into Russian-held territory, while Russia claimed fresh advances in the monthslong battle for the eastern city of Bakhmut.

entries.title: Some Western Backers of Ukraine Worry That Time Might Be on Russia's Side
entries.description: Officials in some capitals fear the Kremlin, which is willing to keep throwing men and materiel into the war, could gain the upper hand in any lengthy war of attrition.

entries.title: Upstart Indian Shipper Helps Get Russian Oil to Market
entries.description: Russia is keeping its oil moving, defying fears that sanctions would lead to a plunge in exports, with the help of several international startups plying new trade routes to mostly Asian buyers.

entries.title: Japan, Netherlands Agree to Limit Exports of Chip-Making Equipment to China
entries.description: The deal with the U.S. advances the Biden administration’s efforts to slow China’s military development by cutting access to advanced technologies.

entries.title: Iran Ammunition Factory Hit by Blast
entries.description: Iran said three drones caused an explosion at an ammunition factory in the central city of Isfahan late Saturday.
